# CLI Usage and Extension

## Using CitrusRules CLI
- The CLI supports these commands:
  ```bash
  # Install globally
  npm install -g citrusrules
  
  # Or use with npx
  npx citrusrules --feature --agent
  
  # Get help
  npx citrusrules --help
  ```
- Current supported flags:
  - `--feature`: Fetches the feature.mdc template
  - `--agent`: Fetches the agent.mdc template

## Extending the CLI
- CLI is implemented using Commander.js in [bin/cli.js](mdc:bin/cli.js)
- To add a new command flag:
  1. Add a new option with description:
     ```javascript
     program
       .option('--new-template', 'Fetch new-template.mdc template');
     ```
  2. Ensure the template exists in the GitHub repository
  3. The flag name should match the template filename (without the .mdc extension)
  4. Follow camelCase for flag names with multiple words (e.g., `--newTemplate`)

## Error Handling
- CLI should handle these error cases:
  - Network errors when fetching templates
  - File system errors when writing templates
  - Invalid flag combinations
- All errors should provide helpful messages with chalk-colored output
